title: For Sale/Trade:  Mossad by Tanfoglio 9mm
location: Mineral Springs, Waxhaw, Charlotte, North Carolina
postcontent:
This is a nice Mossad 9mm pistol.  Made by Tanfoglio in Italy for the Israeli domestic market.  One 16 round mag, 3 dot sights (red front dot, white rear dots), grip area has factory grooves on front and rear for improved grip.  This gun is super comfortable in the hand to shoot and it aims like it is a part of your arm.  Great shooter, I've put maybe 5 mags worth of 9mm through this gun with 0 issues or problems.  Shot several brands of ammo with no problems.  Gun fired all of it great, even the cheap stuff.  Extra mags are easily available online or from most gun shops, the mags are identical for the EEA Witness 9mm full size and the Jericho/Baby Eagle 9mm full size and are interchangeable, thus fairly cheap.  Crisp, smooth trigger, pistol is double or single action and has a frame mounted safety.  These were made in the same valley in Italy as Beretta... the Valley of the Gun they call it.  Nice pattern to the wood grips but they show some wear.  Slide and frame both marked with serial number (not always the case on these).  Gun shows some wear and tear but nothing terrible.  Slide is marked "MOSSAD" and has two six point "Stars of David" on each side of "MOSSAD".  Frame reads as follows: 
Made by Fratelli Tanfoglio S.P.A. For "Weapons house LTD" - Israel
I'll go $350 cash on this one and a quick search online didn't turn up but a couple for sale, and most looked worse condition wise.  Fairly rare gun in the US market, get it while you can!  All laws apply, must have handgun permit or concealed carry.  I wouldn't be selling this if I didn't already have two of these in full size.

title: For Sale/Trade:  VERY NICE 22LR Upper for an AR-15, very accurate, very reliable, top shelf parts.
postcontent:
This upper is a tack driver.  The barrel is a dedicated 16" 22 LR (WASP) barrel by CMMG with a 1:16 twist, the action and collar are all stainless steel (the nicest action sold by CMMG), charging hande is made by CMMG for dedicated 22 uppers.  It has the regular m4 sight base, a magpul moe carbine handguard, and an A2 flash hider (which can be unscrewed by hand to attach your suppressor should you have one.  The upper receiver is a Tactical Innovations AR-15 receiver.  And comes with 2 - 25 round magazines.

This is a cream-of-the-crop build, it is nothing like these cheesy, toy-like dedicated 22 AR's that S&W and Mossberg are putting out, this upper has the look and feel of a real 5.56 upper, it is sturdy, feels great, looks great, shoots fantastic (both accurate and reliable - still yet to jam in the first 300 rounds with the cheap Federal Value pack ammo), yet still in a lightweight package.

This upper is a fantastic training tool for your AR (you can practice at 3-4 cents a round, compared to 25-50 cents a round for 223/556, this adds up very quickly!  You could dump a mag of 22 for the cost of a couple rounds of 223!).  It is accurate enough to be a hunting rifle.  Install on your AR lower takes maybe 10 seconds.  Spare mags can be purchased for $20.

I have exactly $632.31 into this upper, not uncluding the rear sight (Rock River Arms Dominator [$150] and sightmark red dot [$60] which are not included in the $630 price.  I am not looking to make any money on this upper, I am just wanting to start another project.  If you want the rear sights (which are Co-Witness) I would do a package deal at $800.

title: For Sale:  Yugoslavia SKS with Digitech stock and 4x30 scope
postcontent:
I have a yugoslavia SKS with a digitech stock and 4x3o scope. The gun does have a collapsible stock. Also, the Yugoslavia SKS's are able to shoot grenades out of the barrel just like the M1 Garand's. This gun does still have the flip up grenade sites.

No rust, or damage. 

Unlike most SKS rifles the Yugoslavian Sk, has a gas shut off valve. When you fire a gas system rifle the gas pressure will cause the rifle to load another round. However; with a gas shut off valve you can force the gun to fire the single round then be reloaded manually. Just like a Bolt Action Rifle. Simply grab the charging rod pull back and release forward to load your next round from the magazine. The gas release valve is on the Yugoslavia Sk's because, as mentioned before the gun has the ability to fire barrel "mounted" loaded grenades. A special cartridge would be loaded into the magazine and fired striking (I guess) a primer on the grenade. Hence the need for being able to make a semi-automatic rifle, a bolt action rifle when desired.

Call REDACTED for info and or photos.

title: For Sale:  Kel-Tec PF9 package
location: Stuart - Martin County, Florida, United States
postcontent:
Have a PF9 up for trade or sale. About 3 months old. Quite possibly the best carry gun made. Super thin and light.

Done a few things to the gun to improve it. A Kel-Tec is meant to be "finished" by the owner for the most part. All modifications are easily reversible but I doubt you'd want to.

**This gun shoots MUCH nicer than a stock factory gun.**

- Fluff and Buffed. Gun has been broken down and deburred. Slide rails and feed ramp smoothed. Hammer surface smoothed

- Trigger straightened, softened and shortened. Biggest complaint with this gun is the trigger shape from the factory can "pinch" larger fingers. The shorter trigger is MUCH more controllable and softer to shoot. A stock replacement trigger is about 2 bucks from Kel-Tec.

- Hogue grip installed and trimmed. Helps suck up the recoil and improve grip on this little beast.

- +1 extended magazine bottom not only adds a round but vastly improves the gun grip.

- Extra +1 magazine. Any defensive gun needs an extra mag. It also has the +1 extension

- Stainless belt clip. Not installed in the pictures but included. Here is a pic of one installed (mine is stainless, not black) 
http://imgur.com/gTW0w (not my gun)
Installation is very simple 2 screws.

- Sights and hammer painted orange. For some reason the white sights and my eyes did not play nicely. Orange is MUCH easier to see and get on target with. Orange hammer means it is much easier to stage the trigger (along with the shortened trigger) for fast accurate shots. Both are "painted" with my 5 year olds orange nail polish. It's the type that doesn't need remover. Just "peels" off with a toothpick if you don't dig orange. You will though.

- Shimmed rear site. Gun was accurate but this shooter always trended a touch low with it. You may be different. Shim is just a plastic spacer that you can remove if you shoot differently than I do. I'm no marksman.

- Deburred the grip. Has some ridges on it from the factory that can hurt your hands after awhile. An hour with an emery board really smoothed things out.



Also included:

Flat magazine floor plate.

Pinky magazine floor plate (doesn't add a round)

Allen wrench for sight adjustment

Kel-Tec plastic case

Instruction booklets



Not included but possible for the right deal:

Desantis Soft Tuck holster

Uncle Mikes pocket holster



Looking for a compact 9MM such as a Glock 26 or Ruger SR9c. The Kel-Tec is too small for what I need it for now and I have another gun when I need something smaller. Will add cash as needed to the right deal.



A trade is preferred but will sell outright for $360. This is what everything would cost you if you can even find it all plus you'd have to pay tax and shipping.

FTF bill of sale. DL or CWL required.
More photos available upon request.
